---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="Cookie Policy">
  <main class="container my-5">
    <h1>Cookie Policy</h1>
    <p class="lead">
      This Cookie Policy explains how we use cookies and similar technologies on this website.
      It should be read together with our <a href="/privacy-policy">Privacy Policy</a>.
    </p>

    <section class="mt-4">
      <h2>1. What Are Cookies?</h2>
      <p>
        Cookies are small text files placed on your device when you visit a website. They help websites function properly,
        improve security, remember your preferences and provide insights into how the site is used.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mt-4">
      <h2>2. Types of Cookies We Use</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Strictly Necessary Cookies:</strong> Required for core website functionality and security. These cannot be switched off in our systems.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Analytics Cookies:</strong> Help us understand how visitors use our website so we can improve performance and content.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Marketing Cookies:</strong> Used to measure advertising performance and show more relevant campaigns where applicable.
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="mt-4">
      <h2>3. Legal Basis for Cookie Use</h2>
      <p>
        Under UK GDPR and PECR, we use strictly necessary cookies based on our legitimate interests in operating a secure website.
        We only use non-essential cookies (such as analytics or marketing cookies) with your consent.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mt-4">
      <h2>4. Cookie Duration</h2>
      <p>Cookies can be:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Session cookies:</strong> deleted when you close your browser.</li>
        <li><strong>Persistent cookies:</strong> stored for a defined period or until manually removed.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        Cookie lifespan depends on the purpose of each cookie and your browser settings.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mt-4">
      <h2>5. Managing Your Cookie Preferences</h2>
      <p>
        When you first visit this website, you can choose whether to accept or reject non-essential cookies. You can also manage cookies through your browser settings,
        including deleting existing cookies or blocking future cookies.
      </p>
      <p>
        Disabling some cookies may affect your browsing experience and certain site features.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mt-4">
      <h2>6. Third-Party Cookies</h2>
      <p>
        If we use trusted third-party services (for example analytics or embedded media), they may set cookies subject to their own policies.
        Where required, these will only run after your consent.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mt-4">
      <h2>7. Changes to This Cookie Policy</h2>
      <p>
        We may update this policy from time to time to reflect legal, technical or business changes. The latest version will always be published on this page.
      </p>
      <p class="mb-0"><strong>Last updated:</strong> 30 April 2026</p>
    </section>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>